rary texts. An ‘art "ation’ is defined as a reference to a real art work, either by naming, description or allusion. Lexicon-like contributions present the individual ‘galleries’ of 250 German language authors. Exemplary text passages are specified, the corresponding art works are depicted, and the primary and secondary literature is listed. An index provides information about the frequency with which specific art "ations were used in literary history. This book makes a wealth of empirical material systematically available for the first time - both for literary and art scholarship. Published with support of the Fonds zur Förderung der wissenschaftlichen Forschung.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aArt and literature. 0aArtvQuotations, maxims, etc. 0aArtistsvQuotations. 0aGerman literature. 4aBild-Text-Beziehungen. 4aIntermedialität. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aIntermediality.  aModern Literature.  aReception of Art.1 aFliedl, Konstanze, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRauchenbacher, Marina, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWolf, Joanna, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2011z9783110261189oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2011z9783110261240oZDB-23-DGA0 cprintz978311020500840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311025670340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110256703423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110256703/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA